item.title: [Google for Developers] Deep dive on multilinguality in Gemma 3
item.description: Explore Gemma 3 game-changing multilingual capabilities. This video reveals how Gemma 3’s unique architecture allows developers to create AI solutions that break language barriers. From building multilingual chatbots to fine-tuning for specific linguistic styles, you'll learn how to maximize Gemma 3’s potential. Chapters: 0:00 - Introduction 1:56 - Practical examples 3:47 - Get started with Gemma Resources: Gemma documentation → https://goo.gle/3FCVKEJ Gemmaverse → https://goo.gle/4e0KkHz Subscribe to Google for Developers → https://goo.gle/developers Speaker: Adi Mayrav Gilady Products mentioned: Gemma

item.description: Why retrain a model like Gemma? item.title: [Google for Developers] Gemini CLI: Vibe coding and deploying Hello World to Cloud Run!
item.description: Check how our Google Cloud Developer Advocate Luke Schlangen uses Gemini CLI to create a "Hello World" Node.js project and deploy it to Cloud Run, and even troubleshoot common issues—all with commands generated by Gemini CLI itself. See how quick and easy it is to go from an idea to a deployed application! Gemini CLI is an open-source AI agent that brings the power of Gemini directly into your terminal. Individual developers can get started with access to Gemini 2.5 Pro, featuring a 1 million token context window, 60 queries per minute and 20,000 queries per month - all at NO COST. Resources: Install Gemini CLI today→https://goo.gle/46hU0LE Subscribe to Google for Developers → https://goo.gle/developers Products mentioned: Gemini
